    <p class="about-body">I grew up in Houston, TX, where I learned early on that hard work and strong relationships are what open doors. I came to Baylor knowing I wanted to pursue a career in sales, and the ProSales program gave me the tools, the competition, and the community to become the professional I am today.</p>
    <p class="about-body">My dual major in Professional Selling and Risk Management and Insurance was intentional. The insurance industry runs on trust and expertise, and I wanted to understand both the relationship side and the technical side from day one. That combination, paired with my Texas Department of Insurance license, means I am not learning on the job — I am ready to produce.</p>
    <p class="about-body">Outside the classroom and the office, I am deeply involved at Baylor. I hold leadership roles in Kappa Omega Tau and have been part of the Freshman Leadership Organization. I bring the same energy and commitment to everything I am part of, because I believe showing up fully matters, whether it is for a client, a teammate, or a friend.</p>
